name: Highbury East Stand (Avenell Road) - Print
description:
A highly detailed digital illustration depicting the whole of the East stand facade of the now redeveloped ex home ground of Arsenal Football Club.

With it's Deco style architecture, Highbury, in my opinion was the greatest of all the English football grounds. Because of it's cramped location, there are no known photographs of the whole facade, so with the help of lots photographs cobbled together, I was able to produce this piece.

Signed
Limited edition print (1 of 150).
Digitally printed in England on 200gsm uncoated board.
460mm x 320mm

Delivered in a heavy duty cardboard tube.

name: England v West Germany - 1966 World Cup Print
description:
Possibly one of the greatest English sporting events ever. The World Cup final at Wembley, against the old enemy, West Germany. Pitch invasions, the first and only World Cup final hat-trick (so far - 2013) and one dubious goal. England win the 1966 World Cup. A simple, modern illustration commemorating this huge sporting occasion, with the iconic red ball a centre piece.

400 x 300mm
250gsm uncoated board
Printed in England 

Packed in a robust cardboard tube and layered with tissue paper for added protection.

name: Eddy Merckx - Bike Series Print
description:
The first in a possible series of prints. A simple illustration depicting the bike ridden by the great Eddy Merckx accompanied by his achievements at the 3 grand tours. This iconic cyclist is as recognisable as his iconic orange bike.

450 x 320mm
250gsm uncoated board
Printed in England 

Packed in a robust cardboard tube and layered with tissue paper for added protection.
